And lastly, you might find it cliche for me to say.. but i will never stop saying that God will always have your back no matter what you are going through. Because if not for God, i would have never survived living on my own, or moving across the country. All the love and prayers

that no matter how outside people try their best to hurt me, I don’t really care. No one can really break me. No more than how my family can..

but i just also wanna let people realize how lucky they are to just have someone whether a family, a friend, or a significant one.
And this is something that i kind of accepted from a long time ago already but yes this is rare for me to rant due to this momentary “hurt” that I was feeling..

Or how my family lifts up one another when one of them struggles. All of them but me.. or like when i was in Guam on my own when my dad passed away yet i was the one who lifted them up and gave them comfort when they were all together and had each other while i had no one.
i can’t help but notice how other family celebrates their loved ones’ victories no matter how big or small they are..

Or maybe because they have never allowed me to openly show my “weaknesses”.

I somehow feel like them “believing too much” to me is very toxic as well.

I sometimes think that maybe because since i was a kid they’ve always been used to accompanying me on stages receiving medals and recognitions. And that they have never seen me on the behind-the-scenes breaking down, struggling, and failing..

Is it wrong for me to feel like my family has never acknowledged that i’m just a normal person who work hard for everything that I do, everything that I make, or every exam that i take because they’ve always thought i am “naturally gifted” or “too resilient” when things get rough
